TY  - JOUR
T1  - Resistance to Change: The Rest of the Story
AU  - Ford, Jeffrey D.
AU  - Ford, Laurie W.
AU  - D'Amelio, Angelo
Y1  - 2008/04/01
PY  - 2008
DA  - 2008/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2008.31193235
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2008.31193235
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 362
EP  - 377
VL  - 33
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Prevailing views of resistance to change tell a one-sided story that favors change agents by proposing that resistance is an irrational and dysfunctional reaction located ?over there? in change recipients. We tell the rest of the story by proposing that change agents contribute to the occurrence of resistance through their own actions and inactions and that resistance can be a resource for change. We conclude by proposing how resistance might be restructured.
AB  - Prevailing views of resistance to change tell a one-sided story that favors change agents by proposing that resistance is an irrational and dysfunctional reaction located ?over there? in change recipients. We tell the rest of the story by proposing that change agents contribute to the occurrence of resistance through their own actions and inactions and that resistance can be a resource for change. We conclude by proposing how resistance might be restructured.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2008.31193235
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2008.31193235
Y2  - 2026/04/24
